.TH GIT-CLEANUP 1 "2026-01-18" "git-cleanup" "Git Manual"
.SH NAME
git-cleanup \- fetch remote and prune deleted branches
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B git cleanup
.SH DESCRIPTION
Fetch remote references and prune local branches that no longer exist on
the remote. This command combines \fBgit fetch \-\-prune\fR with cleanup of
stale local branches that track origin.
.SH EXAMPLE
.PP
Prune deleted branches:
.PP
.RS
.nf
$ git cleanup
Fetching origin
Deleted branch feature-old (was abc1234).
.fi
.RE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR git-fetch (1),
.BR git-branch (1)
